    "assignees": "David Nickerson",
    "app_url": "https://3.basecamp.com/4226914/buckets/31539020/todos/9670807414",
    "description": "<div>Currently, the both GBPs use this number - (760) 465-8733 <br><br>We need to confirm the correct phone numbers to use across this client’s GBP(s), website, and citations so everything follows our Ideal GBP Phone Number Structure.<br><br><strong>IDEAL GBP &amp; SITE NUMBER STRUCTURE:</strong>\n</div><ul>\n<li>\n<strong>GBP Primary</strong>: Tracking number (<em>if used - only on GBP</em>)</li>\n<li>\n<strong>GBP Secondary</strong>: Local NAPW number (<em>used also across applicable areas on Website + Citations</em>)</li>\n</ul><div>Each location should have <strong>one unique number tied to that office across the web </strong>for NAPW consistency.<br><br><br><strong>INTERNAL CHECK FIRST:</strong><br>I already checked the GBP(s) and website, but couldn’t confirm the correct location numbers.<br><br>Before contacting the client, please check internally for:</div><ul>\n<li>Call Rail access (<em>do location-specific numbers exist?</em>)</li>\n<li>Past client communication</li>\n<li>Internal notes/tasks</li>\n</ul><div>\n<strong>Goal</strong>: see if we can determine the correct numbers <strong>without asking the client first</strong>.<br><br>If we cannot determine the correct numbers internally, we will need to reach out to confirm/obtain a <strong>unique local number for each location</strong>.</div><div>\n<br><strong><br>NUMBER SET UP OPTIONS:</strong>\n</div><div>\n<strong>Preferred</strong>&nbsp;</div><ul>\n<li>GBP Primary: Tracking number</li>\n<li>GBP Secondary: Local NAPW number</li>\n<li>Website + citations use the <strong>local number<br></strong><br>\n</li>\n</ul><div>\n<strong>Also Acceptable</strong><br> If the client only has <strong>one unique number per location</strong>, that number can be used everywhere:&nbsp;</div><ul>\n<li>&nbsp;GBP</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Website</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Citations</li>\n</ul><div>The only downside is that <strong>GBP calls won’t be attributed separately</strong>.&nbsp;</div>",
    "visible_to_clients": false
  },
